ce:section.ce:para:
The samples were cut from medical-grade titanium rods provided by China Baotai Group, with a diameter of 10 mm and a height of 3.5 mm. These titanium rods underwent cutting, grinding, and polishing procedures. The C60 deposition was performed due to high-vacuum sublimation of fullerene C60 powder after evacuating the deposition chamber to a pressure of 1.4·10−6 mbar. The titanium disc sample (Fig. 1
                        , Table 1
                        ) was uniformly coated with C60 for 4 h at 450 °C as described in [5]. For the sample observed in the present study, the fullerene film had a thickness of around 50 nm. The fullerene C60 powder was provided by the Technical University of Ilmenau with a purity of 99.5 %.
